name: Landslide4Sense
description: A globally distributed multi-sensor landslide detection benchmark dataset with 4844 image patches from Sentinel-2 and ALOS PALSAR sensors, organized for machine learning applications in geospatial disaster management.

distribution.name: repo
distribution.description: Local directory containing the Landslide4Sense dataset H5 files. Full file paths are constructed as: {repo_path}/{basePaths.images}/{split}/{filename} for images and {repo_path}/{basePaths.annotations}/{split}/{filename} for annotations.

distribution.name: h5-files-for-config-default
distribution.description: Local H5 files organized in train/test/validation splits.

recordSet.name: default
recordSet.description: Local Landslide4Sense dataset with 3 splits: train (3799 samples), validation (245 samples), test (800 samples)

field.name: default/split
field.description: Split to which the example belongs to.

field.name: default/image
field.description: 14-band multispectral image stack with Sentinel-2 and ALOS PALSAR data

field.name: default/label
field.description: Binary classification label for landslide detection (0: Non-landslide, 1: Landslide)

geographicalBias.description: Dataset covers diverse geographical regions globally but specific locations are not disclosed to prevent data leakage
geographicalBias.mitigation: Globally distributed sampling from multiple continents and climate zones

ethicalConsiderations: Location anonymization to prevent reverse geocoding
Focus on natural disaster mitigation applications
Open source availability for scientific research

geocr:fileListing.note: File paths are now complete relative paths from the dataset root
